    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Limitation of terminado, but it's really hard to do that on Windows. There's a fairly minimal, simple interface on Unix called a pseudoterminal or pty, which communicates between the terminal emulator and the program running in the terminal (like bash). That makes it fairly easy to have a different terminal emulator, which is what we're doing here. On Windows, terminal programs have to call [console API functions](https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms682073.aspx), which makes it much harder to provide a separate console interface.\n\nOh, and I should have been clearer: terminals aren't available if the notebook server is running on Windows. If the server is running on a Unix machine, you can use its terminals in the browser on a Windows machine.\n"
  },
